    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/absolute-hemolysis-index-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index (HI) comparison across all five VAD flow-speed operating conditions",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-measurements",
      "description": "The CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) was compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements conducted at the sponsor's biofluid mechanics laboratory using fresh bovine blood (hematocrit 33±2%) in a closed-loop mock circulatory loop. Five operating points spanning 2.5–6.0 L/min at 2400–3600 RPM were evaluated. Predicted NIH values were extracted from Lagrangian particle-tracking post-processing of the converged RANS solution using the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model with Morrison correction coefficients. Monte Carlo sampling (N=2000) over inlet velocity profile uncertainty and viscosity uncertainty yielded 95% prediction intervals. Comparison metrics included normalized RMS error (nRMSE = 18.3%), coverage of experimental mean values within the 95% PI (4 of 5 operating points), and Bland–Altman limits of agreement (bias −0.0012 g/100 L, LoA ±0.0041 g/100 L). The comparison was judged adequate for credibility purposes by the assessment team at a review meeting held 2025-11-14, with minutes archived in the project quality management system under document QMS-2025-VAD-HI-004. All raw CFD output files, post-processing scripts, and experimental data tables are stored in the project repository at commit hash 9f3a1c7. The outcome supports an achieved credibility level of 3 for Output Comparison under the MRL-5 requirement of 4, representing a documented gap."
    }
  ],
